results.name: Numbers that are 4-persistent but not 5-persistent.
comment: A number n is k-persistent iff all of {n, 2n,..., kn} are pandigital (in the sense of A171102).
link: Hans Havermann, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Persistent Number
xref: Cf. A171102 (pandigital), A204047 (smallest n-persistent), A051264 (1-persistent), A051018 (2-persistent), A051019 (3-persistent), A204096 (5-persistent), A204097 (6-persistent).
